'''Mundra Port Coal Terminal''' is the world's biggest [[coal]] importing terminal. It can handle 40 million tonnes of coal annually. It was built at a cost of [[Rupee|Rs]] 2000 [[crore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/report.asp?newsid=1188706 |title=Adani has made some very 'power'ful moves |publisher=dnaindia.com |date=2008-09-09 |accessdate=2010-03-17}}</ref> It is located at [[Mundra Port]], the largest private port in [[India]].
