'''''México Pelágico''''' is a 2014 Mexican [[documentary film]]. It was written by Jerónimo Prieto, who also directed it.{{r|va}} It portrays the life of the open ocean of Mexico through the eyes of young conservationists.{{r|va}}

It received the Director's Award at the 12th [[San Francisco International Ocean Film Festival]] in early 2015,{{r|sf}} and an audience award for "Best Environmental Film" at the 2015 [[Vail Film Festival]].{{r|va}}

