{{Sidebar|topimage=|style=|name=Ocean Nuclear|title=Ocean Nuclear|heading1=Industry|content1=Finance and Energy|heading2=Native name|content2=海核能源|heading3=Type|content3=private company|heading4=Founded|content4=2017|heading5=Headquarters|content5=Shenzhen, China|heading6=Employees|content6=100|heading7=Key people|content7=Qiu Zhen, chairman|below=}}
'''Ocean Nuclear''' (Chinese: 海核能源) is a financial services provider for the nuclear energy industry. It provides capital market services for energy projects worldwide <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://epaper.21jingji.com/html/2017-11/29/content_75399.htm|title=WNA's youngest member unveiled|last=Shi|first=Yan|date=29 November 2017|website=epaper.21jingji.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-05-23}}</ref> and has negotiated nuclear infrastructure projects in more than 20 countries<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cityam.com/286792/chinese-firm-launches-5bn-london-nuclear-energy-industry|title=Chinese firm launches $5bn London nuclear energy industry fundraising roadshow|last=Mines|first=Josh|date=1 June 2018|work=City AM|access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref>. The company is a member of the [[World Nuclear Association]] (WNA).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-nuclear.org/our-association/membership/our-members.aspx|title=World Nuclear Association Membership|website=World Nuclear Association|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>
== Capital == Ocean Nuclear is currently raising $5bn<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cityam.com/286792/chinese-firm-launches-5bn-london-nuclear-energy-industry|title=Chinese firm launches $5bn London nuclear energy industry fundraising roadshow|last=Mines|first=Josh|date=1 June 2018|work=City AM|access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref> to fund infrastructure projects in nuclear energy.
== Global Nuclear Investment Summit == Ocean Nuclear co-organises the Global Nuclear Investment Summit (GNIS). The first was held in Beijing in January 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://epaper.cbt.com.cn/ep_m/cbtm/html/2018/01/26/05/05_54.htm|title=中国资本助力全球核能产业升级-五版-中华工商时报|website=epaper.cbt.com.cn|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cet.com.cn/gppd/hybk/2003461.shtml|title=The First GNIS Nuclear Energy Investment Forum Successfully Held in Beijing|last=Jiang|first=Shuai|date=1 January 2018|work=China Economic News Network|access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref> The second took place in London in June 2018, in partnership with the [[Financial Times]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Serial-reactor-construction-key-to-lowering-costs-0806184.html|title=Serial reactor construction key to lowering costs|last=World Nuclear News|first=|date=8 June 2018|work=World Nuclear News|access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref>
