The '''Ogishima Solar Power Plant''' (扇島太陽光発電所) is a 13 MW solar [[photovoltaic power station]] located on the waterfront in [[Kawasaki, Kanagawa|Kawasaki]].<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/press/corp-com/release/betu09_e/images/091203e2.pdf Outline]</ref> It is the second, and the largest solar plant built by [[Tokyo Electric Power Company|Tepco]], and was completed on December 19, 2011.<ref>[https://eng.rim-intelligence.co.jp/default/news/print-article/id/82329 TEPCO starts commercial operation of Ogishima solar power plant]</ref> In the first year of operation, it produced 15,059 MWh, a [[capacity factor]] of 0.13,<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/images/121219a.pdf Monthly Total]</ref> which was about 10% greater than anticipated.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/1223759_2266.html The First Anniversary of Ohgishima Solar Power Station, One of the Largest Solar Power Stations in Japan Located in the Coastal Area of Kawasaki City]</ref> An unusual feature of the plant is that the panels are mounted at a fixed angle of 10°, instead of the 30°, which would normally be considered optimal for this latitude.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/challenge/energy/megasolar/index-e.html Tepco real time monitor]</ref>

