{{Infobox organization | name = The Whaleman Foundation | logo = | type = [[501(c)(3)]] | founded_date = | founder = Sam Martelli | location = [[Lahaina, Hawaii]] | origins = | key_people = Jeff Pantukhoff, [[Hayden Panettiere]] | area_served = Global | product = | focus = protection of [[cetacea]]ns ([[whale]]s, [[dolphin]]s, and [[porpoise]]s) | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = | subsib = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = Save the Whales Again! | homepage = {{url|whaleman.org}} | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
'''The Whaleman Foundation''' is a [[non-profit]], [[marine conservation]] organization based in [[Lahaina, Hawaii]] in the United States. It [[Advocacy|advocates]] for the protection of [[cetacea]]ns ([[whale]]s, [[dolphin]]s, and [[porpoise]]s) and their habitats.<ref name="seavoices-pantukhoff">{{cite interview |last = Pantukhoff |first = Jeff |interviewer = Sea Voices |title = Jeff Pantukhoff – Award Winning Underwater Photographer, Whaleman Foundation |type = Book |url = http://seavoices.com/people-i-q/jeff-pantukhoff/ |accessdate = March 15, 2012 |quote = Jeff Pantukhoff is not only an award winning underwater photographer and filmmaker, but the founder of The Whaleman Foundation dedicated to the preservation and protection of cetaceans (dolphins, porpoises and whales) and their habitats. }} </ref><ref name="christianpost-pannettiere"> {{cite news | first = Justin | last = Sarachik | title = Hayden Pannettiere Becomes a Hero Again as an Animal Activist | date = October 14, 2011 | publisher = [[The Christian Post]] | url = http://global.christianpost.com/news/hayden-pannettiere-becomes-a-hero-again-as-an-animal-activist-58199/ | accessdate = March 15, 2012 | quote = '... the founder of the Whaleman Foundation, Jeff Pantukhoff, pulled me aside on the last day and said, "I know you're a fan of animals. Can I show you what I do?"' }}</ref>
Whaleman was founded by Jeff Pantukhoff. [[Hayden Panettiere]] is the spokesperson for the foundation. She has promoted the Foundations' ''Save the Whales Again!'' campaign since 2008. <ref name="time-celebrity-do-gooders">{{cite news | first = Frances | last = Romero | authorlink = | title = Top 10 Celebrity Do-Gooders - Hayden Panettiere | date = June 28, 2010 | publisher = [[Time Inc.]] | url = http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2000036_1999879_1999862,00.html | accessdate = March 15, 2012 | quote = In 2008 she created the "Save the Whales, Again!" campaign }} </ref><ref name="time-celebvocate"> {{cite web | first = | last = | title = Celebvocate: Hayden Panettiere tries to save the whales | date = September 15, 2011 | publisher = [[The Washington Post]] | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/reliable-source/post/celebvocate-hayden-panettiere-tries-to-save-the-whales/2011/09/15/gIQAzVKQVK_blog.html | accessdate = March 15, 2012 | quote = Hayden Panettiere poses with Whaleman Foundation president Jeff Pantukhoff and IWC commissioner Monica Medina beside the White House on Thursday }} </ref><ref name="whitehouse-blog"> {{cite web | first = Hayden | last = Panettiere | title = Protecting Marine Life, Protecting Ourselves | date = September 15, 2011 | publisher = [[whitehouse.gov]] | url = http://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2011/09/15/protecting-marine-life-protecting-ourselves | accessdate = March 15, 2012 | quote = Editor's Note: This blog introduces readers to Hayden Panettiere, who for the past 7 years has been the spokesperson for The Whaleman Foundation and their Save the Whales Again! Campaign. }} </ref><ref name="cnn-interview">{{cite interview |last = Panettiere |first = Hayden |subjectlink = |last2 = Pantukhoff |first2 = Jeff |subjectlink2 = |interviewer = A.J. Hamme; Brooke Anderson |title = Britney and Kevin`s Finances; Prisoners of Fame |url = http://edition.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0711/02/sbt.01.html |work = [[CNN]] Showbiz Tonight