The '''Willwind Wind Farm''' (also sometimes referred to as '''Willpita Wind Farm''') is a small {{Nowrap|850 [[Kilowatt]] (0.85 MW)}} onshore [[wind farm]] built near the village of [[Bithugalgama]], in the [[Ratnapura District]] of [[Sri Lanka]]. The wind farm is owned and operated by {{Nowrap|Willwind (Private) Limited}}. The facility consists of seven [[wind turbine]]s measuring approximately {{nowrap|121 [[Kilowatt|KW]]}} each.<ref>{{cite web|title=SLSEA Energy Permits: Wind Projects|url=http://www.energy.gov.lk/sub_pgs/develop_permits_wind.html|publisher=[[Sri Lanka Sustainable Energy Authority|SLSEA]]|accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>
